1
00:00:10,240 --> 00:00:11,240
Jump down!

2
00:00:12,520 --> 00:00:13,520
Woohoo!

3
00:00:14,160 --> 00:00:16,520
Finally, it's shower time! I stink.

4
00:00:16,760 --> 00:00:17,760
Yay!

5
00:00:18,360 --> 00:00:19,360
I'm scared.

6
00:00:20,200 --> 00:00:21,400
Hurry up. Jump!

7
00:00:21,600 --> 00:00:22,639
Get on, Dum.

8
00:00:22,640 --> 00:00:24,240
Jump in. What are you afraid of?

9
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:26,960
Jump down. Jump.

10
00:00:32,280 --> 00:00:33,720
Hey! Got it.

11
00:00:36,320 --> 00:00:37,759
Where's my sarong?

12
00:00:37,760 --> 00:00:38,760
What's the sarong?

13
00:00:39,360 --> 00:00:40,000
Sarong...

14
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:41,000
What?

15
00:00:41,360 --> 00:00:41,920
Where's it?

16
00:00:41,920 --> 00:00:42,920
Do you want this?

17
00:00:44,120 --> 00:00:46,120
Asshole! Give me my sarong back.

18
00:00:46,640 --> 00:00:51,080
Give me my sarong back.

19
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:56,200
This is not a playground.

20
00:00:57,360 --> 00:00:59,160
If your noise drowns out the alarm,

21
00:00:59,640 --> 00:01:00,920
you won't escape in time.

22
00:01:01,920 --> 00:01:04,160
Especially you, the loudest one.

23
00:01:06,520 --> 00:01:09,000
Let's finish the shower,
so you can have a meal then.

24
00:01:13,256 --> 00:01:13,856
Give me!

25
00:01:13,880 --> 00:01:16,161
Everyone's at it so why the
hell is he scolding me alone?

26
00:01:16,360 --> 00:01:18,839
You're swear again, Comrade Saeng.

27
00:01:18,840 --> 00:01:20,879
They just told us not to swear.

28
00:01:20,880 --> 00:01:21,960
You're gonna get it again.

29
00:02:00,300 --> 00:02:07,300
"When Light Fades"
(Episode 2)

30
00:02:16,240 --> 00:02:18,720
What are you doing?
Why don't you go take a shower?

31
00:02:18,744 --> 00:02:20,864
It gets dark early out
here, unlike in the city.

32
00:02:21,920 --> 00:02:22,920
Understood.

33
00:02:27,840 --> 00:02:28,840
So strict!

34
00:02:34,600 --> 00:02:36,120
Yes, I'm coming.

35
00:02:37,600 --> 00:02:38,600
Hey!

36
00:02:41,360 --> 00:02:44,000
Aren't you going to take
a shower, Comrade Ying?

37
00:02:44,280 --> 00:02:45,680
You'll miss your meal.

38
00:02:46,880 --> 00:02:49,319
I'll do it after putting my things away.

39
00:02:49,320 --> 00:02:51,560
What's your name, sis?

40
00:02:52,240 --> 00:02:54,920
Dad said everyone is equal here.

41
00:02:55,059 --> 00:02:56,899
You can call me Comrade Bai Tong.

42
00:02:57,160 --> 00:02:59,040
Sure, Comrade Bai Tong.

43
00:03:00,560 --> 00:03:05,240
Comrade Bai Tong, do you
know what... a sanitary pad is?

44
00:03:06,400 --> 00:03:07,520
What's a pad?

45
00:03:09,640 --> 00:03:13,800
A sanitary pad is a pad used
to absorb menstrual blood.

46
00:03:17,080 --> 00:03:20,280
Never mind, I'll ask Comrade Roong.

47
00:03:20,880 --> 00:03:23,119
So, if you're free,

48
00:03:23,120 --> 00:03:25,400
could you tell me about the world outside?

49
00:03:26,320 --> 00:03:30,120
Sure, you can ask me
anything you want to know.

50
00:03:30,640 --> 00:03:32,040
Yay!

51
00:03:32,360 --> 00:03:33,360
Let's take a shower.

52
00:03:36,120 --> 00:03:39,359
I'll tell you. Do you know Thai Daimaru?

53
00:03:39,360 --> 00:03:41,080
It's a department store, it has everything.

54
00:03:48,200 --> 00:03:49,480
Is it edible?

55
00:03:49,960 --> 00:03:54,080
Sure. It's a blessing to
find some food in the forest.

56
00:03:55,480 --> 00:03:56,800
How do I eat this?

57
00:03:57,480 --> 00:04:00,200
We eat to live, not live to eat.

58
00:04:02,400 --> 00:04:03,760
That hits hard, comrade.

59
00:04:04,440 --> 00:04:05,440
Next.

60
00:04:05,960 --> 00:04:06,960
Thanks.

61
00:04:10,280 --> 00:04:10,880
Are you alright?

62
00:04:11,040 --> 00:04:12,000
Comrade Meut.

63
00:04:12,040 --> 00:04:13,040
Huh?

64
00:04:13,280 --> 00:04:15,160
I think we should stay
away from Comrade Saeng.

65
00:04:15,240 --> 00:04:16,240
Why?

66
00:04:16,640 --> 00:04:18,080
Or else we'll all be in trouble too.

67
00:04:18,720 --> 00:04:19,720
Good point.

68
00:04:20,560 --> 00:04:21,560
So much for being a team.

69
00:04:37,560 --> 00:04:38,560
Mada...

70
00:04:40,240 --> 00:04:41,440
Why did you come late?

71
00:04:43,073 --> 00:04:44,193
I had a little stomachache.

72
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:47,000
Go grab a plate.

73
00:04:49,240 --> 00:04:51,720
It's kinda like porridge, I guess.

74
00:04:52,040 --> 00:04:54,960
This is Comrade Saeng.

75
00:04:55,440 --> 00:04:57,680
This is Comrade Bai Tong,
a daughter of Comrade Ploeng.

76
00:04:58,440 --> 00:05:01,080
Comrade Bai Tong, can I
change the menu next time?

77
00:05:01,400 --> 00:05:03,479
Eating porridge and yams is unbearable.

78
00:05:03,480 --> 00:05:06,560
Sure, then eat boiled
yams and porridge tomorrow.

79
00:05:07,040 --> 00:05:08,520
What's the difference?

80
00:05:08,720 --> 00:05:10,680
We eat to live, not live to eat.

81
00:05:11,560 --> 00:05:13,040
That line again!

82
00:05:17,760 --> 00:05:18,760
Deal with it.

83
00:05:20,360 --> 00:05:22,480
You'll get used to it, if you eat often.

84
00:05:34,520 --> 00:05:36,680
My dear comrades.

85
00:05:39,160 --> 00:05:42,039
Our goal and ideology

86
00:05:42,040 --> 00:05:45,320
are not only fighting
against the government,

87
00:05:46,800 --> 00:05:50,040
but we fight against injustice,

88
00:05:50,257 --> 00:05:51,496
and inequality.

89
00:05:51,520 --> 00:05:53,199
We also fight against poverty

90
00:05:53,200 --> 00:05:55,080
that oppresses the people in the country.

91
00:05:55,240 --> 00:05:57,200
To all of my beloved comrades,

92
00:05:57,800 --> 00:06:00,759
I want you to learn everything

93
00:06:00,760 --> 00:06:03,080
from our base as much as possible.

94
00:06:03,280 --> 00:06:05,600
So all of you can become the main force...

95
00:06:06,120 --> 00:06:08,920
to improve our country.

96
00:06:09,213 --> 00:06:13,053
Male comrades, while you're here,

97
00:06:13,213 --> 00:06:17,053
if you have any questions,
please ask Comrade Yue.

98
00:06:19,960 --> 00:06:23,560
Female comrades, please ask Comrade Roong.

99
00:06:23,920 --> 00:06:28,919
A topic like a romance - who loves whom.

100
00:06:29,033 --> 00:06:32,273
Must be reported to the responsible comrade.

101
00:06:32,773 --> 00:06:34,773
Me and Comrade Ying, we're dating.

102
00:06:37,380 --> 00:06:39,339
Dating? What is this?

103
00:06:40,840 --> 00:06:42,520
It means we are lovers.

104
00:06:46,419 --> 00:06:48,539
Why do we have to report who loves whom?

105
00:06:49,573 --> 00:06:51,852
So the leader knows,

106
00:06:52,200 --> 00:06:54,560
and can help resolve any issues.

107
00:06:54,760 --> 00:06:55,839
When two people are in love..

108
00:06:55,840 --> 00:06:57,479
Why do we need anyone else to handle this?

109
00:06:57,480 --> 00:06:59,440
Don't interrupt while
Comrade Ploeng is speaking.

110
00:07:00,560 --> 00:07:02,720
I'm not, I already raised my hand first.

111
00:07:03,160 --> 00:07:06,160
It's OK, go ahead and ask.

112
00:07:08,280 --> 00:07:09,640
That kid is mischievous.

113
00:07:18,520 --> 00:07:20,960
Does anybody know about
The Three Delays Policy?

114
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:22,720
I do.

115
00:07:22,960 --> 00:07:24,799
The Three Delays Policy is delayed love,

116
00:07:24,800 --> 00:07:26,400
delayed marriage, delayed childbirth.

117
00:07:26,600 --> 00:07:28,479
Love causes chaos.

118
00:07:28,480 --> 00:07:30,479
The Party wants everyone
to focus on their work

119
00:07:30,480 --> 00:07:32,360
and devote themselves to the mission first.

120
00:07:32,640 --> 00:07:34,039
He already knows.

121
00:07:34,040 --> 00:07:36,480
That's it, why does he need
to tell that he has a girlfirend?

122
00:07:36,560 --> 00:07:37,639
Yeah, that's right.

123
00:07:37,640 --> 00:07:40,200
Good. Sit down.

124
00:07:41,600 --> 00:07:46,720
Tonight please take a full rest, dismissed.

125
00:08:06,960 --> 00:08:09,119
I get what The Three Delays Policy is.

126
00:08:09,120 --> 00:08:11,640
But the feeling is hard to resist.

127
00:08:12,240 --> 00:08:13,480
They don't forbid it,

128
00:08:13,800 --> 00:08:16,200
they just want to slow things down.

129
00:08:17,400 --> 00:08:19,760
Nobody can resist it forever.

130
00:08:20,880 --> 00:08:23,040
They say there's no rules here,

131
00:08:23,360 --> 00:08:25,120
but in the end,
there's still restrictions.

132
00:08:25,560 --> 00:08:27,559
That's what happens when you
have to manage a lot of people.

133
00:08:27,560 --> 00:08:29,600
Every place needs rules to control people.

134
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:32,840
I get it, but I don't accept it.

135
00:08:35,160 --> 00:08:37,359
You oppose The Three Delays Policy,

136
00:08:37,360 --> 00:08:39,520
as if you're in love with someone.

137
00:08:39,960 --> 00:08:40,999
Are you seeing someone?

138
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:42,960
Are you?

139
00:08:43,040 --> 00:08:43,520
Tell us.

140
00:08:43,521 --> 00:08:46,840
No, no, no, not yet.

141
00:08:47,640 --> 00:08:51,679
I wanna know who can
stir comrade Sang's heart.

142
00:08:51,680 --> 00:08:53,639
Who will it be?

143
00:08:53,640 --> 00:08:56,400
Anyone who makes me feel comfortable.

144
00:08:57,400 --> 00:08:59,920
But now we should focus on our goal, right?

145
00:08:59,960 --> 00:09:02,119
How to make our country better.

146
00:09:02,120 --> 00:09:03,560
That's all.

147
00:09:05,480 --> 00:09:06,960
Three of us,

148
00:09:07,160 --> 00:09:08,600
we will make it happen.

149
00:09:09,440 --> 00:09:10,720
Deal?

150
00:09:10,760 --> 00:09:12,080
Deal.

151
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:14,360
Great.

152
00:09:16,840 --> 00:09:18,160
I don't like Comrade Saeng.

153
00:09:19,080 --> 00:09:20,720
He's been mouthing off since he got here.

154
00:09:24,240 --> 00:09:25,720
You haven't even known him for a day.

155
00:09:26,080 --> 00:09:27,320
You're already judging him?

156
00:09:31,793 --> 00:09:33,033
You're protecting him, right?

157
00:09:38,440 --> 00:09:39,680
It's a fact.

158
00:09:43,360 --> 00:09:44,600
Do you know

159
00:09:45,040 --> 00:09:47,840
that Comrade Saeng has the
same last name as that cop?

160
00:09:54,640 --> 00:09:56,239
Too bad,

161
00:09:56,240 --> 00:09:58,521
The student information has been kept
with Comrade Ploeng.

162
00:09:59,417 --> 00:10:00,856
Otherwise, we would know right away.

163
00:10:00,880 --> 00:10:02,360
So there's no need to keep wondering.

164
00:10:07,240 --> 00:10:08,520
I guess not.

165
00:10:11,520 --> 00:10:13,440
This guy doesn't look like a bad cop.

166
00:11:41,320 --> 00:11:42,600
Dad!

167
00:12:02,680 --> 00:12:04,480
I'd better go. See you at the courtyard.

168
00:12:05,280 --> 00:12:06,679
Come quickly.

169
00:12:06,680 --> 00:12:08,120
OK. I'll catch up with you.

170
00:12:10,400 --> 00:12:12,439
Oh! Good morning, Comrade Yue.

171
00:12:12,440 --> 00:12:13,800
Hello, Comrade Yue.

172
00:12:16,560 --> 00:12:17,999
Wake up, Comrade Saeng!

173
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:19,920
Hmm... just a minute.

174
00:12:20,080 --> 00:12:21,200
Please hurry.

175
00:12:21,520 --> 00:12:22,520
Yeah!

176
00:12:22,920 --> 00:12:23,920
Hello, Comrade.

177
00:12:29,560 --> 00:12:30,560
Comrade Saeng.

178
00:12:38,160 --> 00:12:39,160
Ahem!

179
00:12:39,560 --> 00:12:40,560
Comrade Saeng.

180
00:12:40,920 --> 00:12:42,360
Give me two secs.

181
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:49,000
So drowsy!

182
00:13:31,280 --> 00:13:32,480
Stop being drowsy.

183
00:13:33,680 --> 00:13:35,961
Do you want all the comrades
at the base to wait for you?

184
00:13:47,240 --> 00:13:51,840
Shit! Is it the end of the
world? I just woke up late.

185
00:13:52,480 --> 00:13:53,480
I hear you.

186
00:13:57,920 --> 00:13:59,880
Good, Comrade Yue.

187
00:14:00,320 --> 00:14:02,000
I'm coming now.

188
00:14:12,760 --> 00:14:14,000
Well, comrades,

189
00:14:14,720 --> 00:14:16,960
It's time to get your bodies strong.

190
00:14:17,640 --> 00:14:21,480
Brace yourselves to join
a grand mission together.

191
00:14:21,600 --> 00:14:23,600
Ready? Repeat after me:

192
00:14:24,480 --> 00:14:30,120
Waist, shoulder, head, shoulder, waist.

193
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:32,000
After walking this far,

194
00:14:32,001 --> 00:14:33,400
we still have to do this.

195
00:14:35,560 --> 00:14:38,759
If we are strong, and tough,

196
00:14:38,760 --> 00:14:41,839
we will have a strength
to fight the opponent.

197
00:14:41,840 --> 00:14:42,480
Come on!

198
00:14:42,720 --> 00:14:43,959
Ho! Hey!

199
00:14:43,960 --> 00:14:44,760
How does he hear it?

200
00:14:44,761 --> 00:14:52,199
Ho! Hey! Ho! Hey!

201
00:14:52,200 --> 00:14:53,959
Louder! Yes!

202
00:14:53,960 --> 00:14:55,640
You're standing still though, Comrade Yue.

203
00:14:56,920 --> 00:14:59,040
You're standing still though, Comrade Yue.

204
00:15:00,640 --> 00:15:01,879
Switch to another exercise.

205
00:15:01,880 --> 00:15:03,160
Arm circles.

206
00:15:04,440 --> 00:15:05,720
Arm circles.

207
00:15:06,400 --> 00:15:07,680
Arm circles.

208
00:15:08,120 --> 00:15:09,400
Arm circles.

209
00:15:13,960 --> 00:15:15,240
Remember to shout Hey!

210
00:15:15,440 --> 00:15:16,520
Hey! Hey!

211
00:15:17,080 --> 00:15:18,160
Hey! Hey!

212
00:15:18,960 --> 00:15:20,199
Change position.

213
00:15:20,200 --> 00:15:20,800
Everybody.

214
00:15:20,801 --> 00:15:22,680
Time to backbend.

215
00:15:23,720 --> 00:15:24,720
Get in pairs.

216
00:15:25,120 --> 00:15:25,480
Look.

217
00:15:25,480 --> 00:15:26,040
Urgh!

218
00:15:26,120 --> 00:15:27,559
Urgh!

219
00:15:27,560 --> 00:15:29,320
Like this.

220
00:15:29,560 --> 00:15:30,839
Urgh!

221
00:15:30,840 --> 00:15:36,320
Urgh!

222
00:15:37,240 --> 00:15:38,440
Comrade Yue.

223
00:15:38,520 --> 00:15:40,600
Help Comrade Saeng adjust his posture.

224
00:15:41,480 --> 00:15:42,480
Quick!

225
00:15:48,840 --> 00:15:50,960
Ouch!

226
00:15:53,040 --> 00:15:58,040
Argh!

227
00:16:00,840 --> 00:16:02,479
The newcomer students,

228
00:16:02,480 --> 00:16:04,200
they are a good force...

229
00:16:04,680 --> 00:16:06,279
to improve our troop.

230
00:16:06,280 --> 00:16:07,480
Make us stronger.

231
00:16:08,040 --> 00:16:09,519
We have to categorize them

232
00:16:09,520 --> 00:16:12,720
by their knowledge and abilities.

233
00:16:15,920 --> 00:16:18,959
Comrade Gaun Hin joined a
group with Comrade Saeng.

234
00:16:18,960 --> 00:16:21,160
He was a university's leader.

235
00:16:21,280 --> 00:16:24,480
He has a fair amount of
knowledge in administration.

236
00:16:25,120 --> 00:16:26,679
If he works with the masses,

237
00:16:26,680 --> 00:16:29,080
He could become one of our key people.

238
00:16:29,600 --> 00:16:33,159
Send Comrade Guan
Hin to the Political Unit.

239
00:16:33,160 --> 00:16:34,920
Working with masses

240
00:16:35,280 --> 00:16:36,959
can help him understand the villagers,

241
00:16:36,960 --> 00:16:39,240
so he can persuade them
to join our movement.

242
00:16:40,960 --> 00:16:45,280
From what I've seen in her background,

243
00:16:45,520 --> 00:16:47,800
Comrade Ying studied education.

244
00:16:48,520 --> 00:16:51,519
Should we send her to the Education Unit?

245
00:16:51,520 --> 00:16:52,919
Comrade Ying is a calm person.

246
00:16:52,920 --> 00:16:55,680
But we're short-staffed at
the Medical Unit right now.

247
00:16:56,920 --> 00:16:57,920
Good.

248
00:16:58,200 --> 00:16:59,200
So,

249
00:16:59,840 --> 00:17:03,319
Let Comrade Ying use her medical knowledge

250
00:17:03,320 --> 00:17:05,600
to persuade the masses to join us too.

251
00:17:08,720 --> 00:17:09,720
What about Comrade Saeng?

252
00:17:10,680 --> 00:17:12,680
He's a stubborn, hard to control.

253
00:17:12,920 --> 00:17:14,360
He could cause trouble for us.

254
00:17:14,400 --> 00:17:16,280
We shouldn't let him do an important task.

255
00:17:17,040 --> 00:17:18,480
But if we listen to his opinion,

256
00:17:19,240 --> 00:17:21,200
we could gain a new perspective on work.

257
00:17:21,480 --> 00:17:22,640
A weird perspective, I guess.

258
00:17:23,360 --> 00:17:24,440
Always breaking every rule.

259
00:17:25,120 --> 00:17:26,120
No.

260
00:17:26,560 --> 00:17:28,680
Relax, Comrade Fah.

261
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:33,240
All hits, Comrade!

262
00:17:36,840 --> 00:17:39,640
The person who dares to think and question,

263
00:17:40,160 --> 00:17:43,560
and knows their way around
weapons, is interesting.

264
00:17:45,880 --> 00:17:48,079
If we train him some more,

265
00:17:48,080 --> 00:17:50,320
he could be our new leader in the future.

266
00:17:52,680 --> 00:17:55,800
Well, let's send Comrade
Saeng to the Military Unit.

267
00:17:56,200 --> 00:17:57,800
He will be able to train both physically

268
00:17:57,960 --> 00:18:01,560
and in communication and mission planning.

269
00:18:02,840 --> 00:18:04,000
Yes, sir.

270
00:18:11,240 --> 00:18:12,360
If you'll excuse me.

271
00:18:23,840 --> 00:18:26,160
It has been a month since
the student crackdown,

272
00:18:27,920 --> 00:18:31,039
but the domestic communist
forces are growing stronger.

273
00:18:31,040 --> 00:18:33,520
Especially the students
who fled into the forests

274
00:18:33,920 --> 00:18:35,760
they've become key allies.

275
00:18:36,360 --> 00:18:38,400
They use a "forest
surrounding the city" strategy,

276
00:18:38,720 --> 00:18:40,359
setting up bases in the country,

277
00:18:40,360 --> 00:18:42,000
and stirring villagers against the state.

278
00:18:42,960 --> 00:18:45,160
We can't let it go on.

279
00:18:45,560 --> 00:18:48,120
Our mission is to wipe
them out as soon as possible.

280
00:18:58,400 --> 00:19:00,080
Dan.

281
00:19:03,026 --> 00:19:06,106
The student leaders that
you asked me to search for...

282
00:19:07,520 --> 00:19:08,959
Have you heard anything?

283
00:19:08,960 --> 00:19:11,240
My team member said
they're at northern region.

284
00:19:12,880 --> 00:19:14,399
Just because I'm keeping
track of the situation,

285
00:19:14,400 --> 00:19:17,440
it doesn't mean I
agree with those kids.

286
00:19:20,480 --> 00:19:22,039
Dad, Vin and those students,

287
00:19:22,040 --> 00:19:23,479
they are not criminals.

288
00:19:23,480 --> 00:19:25,399
But they are on the other side.

289
00:19:25,400 --> 00:19:27,480
You should be aware of
your own standpoint too.

290
00:19:59,040 --> 00:20:00,840
Your aim has improved a lot.

291
00:20:02,680 --> 00:20:04,840
I have a talent. It's
a piece of cake, bro.

292
00:20:26,680 --> 00:20:28,240
Stop shooting, Comrades.

293
00:20:29,560 --> 00:20:31,000
Comrade Ploeng.

294
00:20:32,240 --> 00:20:33,279
What's going on?

295
00:20:33,686 --> 00:20:35,486
There's news from the main base.

296
00:20:49,760 --> 00:20:52,400
Comrade Ploeng, you can handle it.

297
00:20:52,800 --> 00:20:55,081
Comrades, please continue
training. I'll take care of it.

298
00:20:57,600 --> 00:21:01,360
The main base has given orders
to send all new comrades...

299
00:21:01,440 --> 00:21:03,240
to recruit more of the masses.

300
00:21:04,480 --> 00:21:06,880
Comrade Phu Pha, please
inform Comrade Yaguar.

301
00:21:07,320 --> 00:21:10,480
Prepare to lead all new
comrades into the village.

302
00:21:11,080 --> 00:21:12,359
Yes, sir.

303
00:21:12,360 --> 00:21:13,480
Comrade Yue,

304
00:21:13,880 --> 00:21:17,040
I want you to train Comrade Saeng
in shooting a bit more.

305
00:21:17,440 --> 00:21:19,040
He is very promising.

306
00:21:19,440 --> 00:21:20,640
Sure, Comrade Ploeng.

307
00:21:21,880 --> 00:21:22,720
Letting a newbie

308
00:21:22,720 --> 00:21:23,720
join the army...

309
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:25,399
without knowing his background.

310
00:21:25,400 --> 00:21:26,480
I think it's too risky.

311
00:21:26,840 --> 00:21:28,200
I've already checked.

312
00:21:28,720 --> 00:21:30,360
His profile is clean.

313
00:21:31,600 --> 00:21:33,920
We have the talented kid in our base,

314
00:21:34,480 --> 00:21:36,840
we must use his abilities to our advantage.

315
00:21:37,840 --> 00:21:39,279
In the future,

316
00:21:39,280 --> 00:21:42,600
he could become a new
main force for our base.

317
00:21:44,640 --> 00:21:47,080
Comrade Ying, she's quite capable.

318
00:21:47,320 --> 00:21:49,519
Train her a bit more and once
she's more comfortable,

319
00:21:49,706 --> 00:21:51,946
she can help ease Comrade Roong's workload.

320
00:21:52,520 --> 00:21:54,319
Do you want to train Comrade Ying

321
00:21:54,320 --> 00:21:55,520
to replace Comrade Roong?

322
00:21:56,560 --> 00:22:01,040
Is this bad to add new talents in the base?

323
00:22:02,600 --> 00:22:04,959
Don't think about who will replace whom;

324
00:22:05,319 --> 00:22:09,399
that kind of thinking won't get us far.

325
00:22:12,680 --> 00:22:14,080
Do you get it?

326
00:22:19,040 --> 00:22:20,440
Yes, sir.

327
00:22:41,840 --> 00:22:43,240
Oh, Dan.

328
00:22:45,240 --> 00:22:46,640
Hello, Aunt La-or.

329
00:22:46,680 --> 00:22:48,520
What are you doing here?

330
00:22:48,619 --> 00:22:49,939
I was just in the area,

331
00:22:50,000 --> 00:22:51,319
I thought I'd come pick you up.

332
00:22:51,320 --> 00:22:53,880
I also have something to talk to.

333
00:22:59,240 --> 00:23:02,399
Hey! Read it so you
know what they're up to.

334
00:23:02,400 --> 00:23:04,760
Our children won't become their tools.

335
00:23:04,800 --> 00:23:05,800
Rumor has it that... (Hanging with
Communists is like holding a serpent.)

336
00:23:05,801 --> 00:23:07,856
They brainwash people, (Hanging with
Communists is like holding a serpent.)

337
00:23:07,880 --> 00:23:08,720
telling them not to worship monks,

338
00:23:08,721 --> 00:23:09,959
to not respect their parents.

339
00:23:09,960 --> 00:23:10,960
Whoa!

340
00:23:11,440 --> 00:23:13,239
They say if you find
those Red-Flag bastards,

341
00:23:13,240 --> 00:23:15,640
you can shoot them before asking.

342
00:23:17,520 --> 00:23:20,080
Hi, kid.

343
00:23:20,680 --> 00:23:22,239
You have to be very careful of them.

344
00:23:22,240 --> 00:23:23,279
Never trust a stranger.

345
00:23:23,280 --> 00:23:24,920
Why don't they think that...

346
00:23:24,960 --> 00:23:27,720
the students who fled to
the forest, are just innocent?

347
00:23:28,720 --> 00:23:30,720
They are our children.

348
00:23:32,760 --> 00:23:34,760
I might disagree with Vin,

349
00:23:35,600 --> 00:23:38,920
but I believe that Vin
is not what others say.

350
00:23:39,600 --> 00:23:41,280
Aunt La-or. I...

351
00:23:41,960 --> 00:23:44,999
I heard that Vin might be at the base
in the northern region.

352
00:23:45,000 --> 00:23:47,360
I'm going to be on duty there.

353
00:23:48,800 --> 00:23:51,160
If I see him I'll definitely inform you.

354
00:23:54,680 --> 00:23:56,240
Thank you so much, Dan.

355
00:23:59,520 --> 00:24:04,320
Dan, I want to give him
something through you.

356
00:24:07,320 --> 00:24:08,920
No problem, Aunt La-or.

357
00:24:11,400 --> 00:24:12,760
Thank you.

358
00:24:13,200 --> 00:24:14,560
You're welcome.

359
00:24:20,520 --> 00:24:24,120
Stealth movement training
means moving as quietly as possible

360
00:24:24,360 --> 00:24:25,480
on the battlefield.

361
00:24:26,120 --> 00:24:28,000
The moment the enemy knows our spot,

362
00:24:29,720 --> 00:24:32,680
we turn from hunters into the hunted.

363
00:24:35,280 --> 00:24:37,600
Wherever I hear a sound,

364
00:24:38,480 --> 00:24:39,480
Ouch!

365
00:24:39,920 --> 00:24:40,920
Ouch!

366
00:24:44,680 --> 00:24:45,920
I'll shoot.

367
00:24:48,120 --> 00:24:51,839
If I hear any movement from you next time,
I won't aim at your body,

368
00:24:51,840 --> 00:24:53,840
but straight at the forehead.

369
00:24:57,240 --> 00:24:58,240
Ouch!

370
00:25:02,360 --> 00:25:04,120
Whoever reaches the big tree first

371
00:25:04,320 --> 00:25:05,600
will receive a reward from me.

372
00:25:39,360 --> 00:25:40,360
Whoa!

373
00:25:54,560 --> 00:25:55,560
What's wrong with you?

374
00:26:06,720 --> 00:26:08,080
I reached it first.

375
00:26:08,600 --> 00:26:09,920
Where's my reward?

376
00:26:13,600 --> 00:26:14,920
Do you have it?

377
00:26:26,240 --> 00:26:27,600
A banana?

378
00:26:28,480 --> 00:26:30,400
I run for a mile, just to get a banana?

379
00:26:31,240 --> 00:26:32,240
That's the reward.

380
00:26:32,600 --> 00:26:33,600
A reward?

381
00:26:33,800 --> 00:26:35,640
Eat it. You'll gain more strength to run.

382
00:26:37,800 --> 00:26:38,800
Comrade!

383
00:26:40,960 --> 00:26:43,280
I've seen Thai soldiers patrolling nearby.

384
00:26:48,033 --> 00:26:49,439
Take everyone back to the base.

385
00:26:49,440 --> 00:26:50,639
I'll check on it.

386
00:26:50,640 --> 00:26:51,440
I'll go with you.

387
00:26:51,441 --> 00:26:52,840
No, you won't.

388
00:26:53,800 --> 00:26:55,120
The rest of you follow me.

389
00:26:56,480 --> 00:26:57,800
Go.

390
00:27:07,600 --> 00:27:08,880
Why are you following me?

391
00:27:08,920 --> 00:27:10,240
Go back to the base.

392
00:27:10,600 --> 00:27:11,160
But...

393
00:27:11,160 --> 00:27:12,160
That's an order.

394
00:28:03,840 --> 00:28:05,200
You arrived later than I thought.

395
00:28:05,800 --> 00:28:06,800
Oh!

396
00:28:07,320 --> 00:28:08,560
How did you get here before us?

397
00:28:09,200 --> 00:28:11,880
What about the Thai soldiers?

398
00:28:13,680 --> 00:28:15,600
The soldiers can't intrude on our base.

399
00:28:16,880 --> 00:28:19,680
Actually, another comrade
is practicing shooting.

400
00:28:24,520 --> 00:28:25,599
This is just a test.

401
00:28:25,600 --> 00:28:28,880
In a real situation,
whoever panics will die.

402
00:28:34,720 --> 00:28:36,200
Where's Comrade Saeng?

403
00:28:36,480 --> 00:28:37,760
Well...

404
00:28:38,360 --> 00:28:39,400
Where is he?

405
00:28:44,520 --> 00:28:47,159
You two, head to the stream we just left.

406
00:28:47,160 --> 00:28:49,759
Both of you, search at the
yard where we had practiced.

407
00:28:49,760 --> 00:28:51,160
I'll search along the path.

408
00:28:56,640 --> 00:28:58,040
Comrade Yue!

409
00:29:01,200 --> 00:29:02,600
Comrade Yue!

410
00:29:05,680 --> 00:29:07,080
Comrade Yue!

411
00:29:18,680 --> 00:29:21,200
Comrade Yue!

412
00:29:21,640 --> 00:29:23,240
Comrade Yue!

413
00:29:24,280 --> 00:29:25,920
Comrade Yue!

414
00:29:44,760 --> 00:29:46,400
Comrade Yue!

415
00:30:06,080 --> 00:30:07,720
Help me.

416
00:30:10,800 --> 00:30:12,440
Arghhhhhh!!!!

417
00:30:20,800 --> 00:30:22,000
Comrade Saeng!

418
00:30:24,560 --> 00:30:25,600
Comrade Saeng!

419
00:30:36,240 --> 00:30:37,440
Comrade Saeng!

420
00:30:57,920 --> 00:30:59,120
Comrade Saeng!

421
00:31:04,560 --> 00:31:05,760
Comrade Saeng!

422
00:31:10,000 --> 00:31:11,200
Comrade Saeng!

423
00:31:18,360 --> 00:31:19,560
It's me. Comrade Saeng.

424
00:31:24,160 --> 00:31:25,360
Comrade Saeng.

425
00:31:33,360 --> 00:31:34,560
It's me.

426
00:31:45,880 --> 00:31:47,080
Comrade Yue!

427
00:31:48,920 --> 00:31:50,120
Where have you been?

428
00:31:50,800 --> 00:31:52,000
I've been trying to find you.

429
00:31:55,720 --> 00:31:56,920
It's OK, Comrade Saeng.

430
00:32:16,320 --> 00:32:19,240
If I'm here, you'll be fine.

431
00:32:29,480 --> 00:32:30,720
Go back to the base.

432
00:32:47,080 --> 00:32:48,080
Get on my back.

433
00:32:48,120 --> 00:32:49,120
Get on your back?

434
00:32:49,120 --> 00:32:50,120
Get on my back.

435
00:33:18,520 --> 00:33:21,200
This area is all Hmong villages.

436
00:33:21,440 --> 00:33:22,360
Where are you going?

437
00:33:22,383 --> 00:33:23,383
Gathering some forest stuff.

438
00:33:23,440 --> 00:33:24,440
I see.

439
00:33:25,440 --> 00:33:26,440
Good luck!

440
00:33:27,760 --> 00:33:30,719
The path to the left leads up the mountain.

441
00:33:30,720 --> 00:33:32,959
And the right leads to the stream.

442
00:33:32,960 --> 00:33:37,320
As for this route... that side
uses it to transport supplies.

443
00:33:39,200 --> 00:33:40,200
Supplies?

444
00:33:43,480 --> 00:33:44,480
Shi Wang.

445
00:33:47,800 --> 00:33:48,800
Ma'am.

446
00:33:50,360 --> 00:33:51,080
Do you know where she lives?

447
00:33:51,120 --> 00:33:52,120
Yes, I do.

448
00:33:53,480 --> 00:33:55,120
Do you want me to send more rice, elder?

449
00:33:55,600 --> 00:33:57,919
My family barely has
enough to eat as it is.

450
00:33:57,920 --> 00:34:00,680
Whether you have it or not,
that's not my damn business!

451
00:34:01,040 --> 00:34:04,120
If you don't want
trouble, then do as I say.

452
00:34:05,040 --> 00:34:07,719
Please, I beg of you, Please help me!

453
00:34:07,720 --> 00:34:09,840
Yaguar.. Yaguar.. Your mother fainted!

454
00:34:10,760 --> 00:34:12,680
Mother! Mother!

455
00:34:13,640 --> 00:34:14,560
Let's go inside first.

456
00:34:14,560 --> 00:34:15,560
Mother!

457
00:34:18,040 --> 00:34:19,719
Your mother fainted. Luckily,

458
00:34:19,720 --> 00:34:21,720
this gentleman helped her just in time.

459
00:34:25,386 --> 00:34:27,666
Thank you so much for saving my mother.

460
00:34:29,320 --> 00:34:30,599
But... who are you?

461
00:34:30,600 --> 00:34:32,400
I've never seen your
face around here before.

462
00:34:33,920 --> 00:34:35,320
He's from Bangkok.

463
00:34:35,560 --> 00:34:37,760
He's here looking for land
to grow vegetables for sale.

464
00:34:40,720 --> 00:34:42,160
Thank you again.

465
00:34:43,840 --> 00:34:47,400
We should head back now.
Let your mother get some rest.

466
00:34:54,960 --> 00:34:56,439
If she doesn't get any better,

467
00:34:56,440 --> 00:34:58,000
have Yang Sue come and tell me.

468
00:34:59,680 --> 00:35:02,880
Thank you, sir. You're a truly good man.

469
00:35:05,320 --> 00:35:08,920
Was there trouble earlier?
Things looked a bit tense.

470
00:35:17,400 --> 00:35:21,560
It's about the rice.
This field I'm farming... it's not mine.

471
00:35:23,520 --> 00:35:25,519
I have to give a portion to the landlord,

472
00:35:25,520 --> 00:35:27,560
and another to the village chief.

473
00:35:28,200 --> 00:35:31,760
Whatever's left is all we have to eat.

474
00:35:37,920 --> 00:35:39,520
Sometimes I don't understand.

475
00:35:40,520 --> 00:35:43,280
My mother and I work ourselves
to death in the rice fields.

476
00:35:45,360 --> 00:35:47,840
But we only get to
eat a little bit of the rice.

477
00:35:50,800 --> 00:35:54,520
That's how it is. We
have no rights, no voice.

478
00:36:03,440 --> 00:36:06,880
I've heard how hard it
is for the people here.

479
00:36:10,280 --> 00:36:13,000
But seeing it for
myself... it's no surprise,

480
00:36:14,800 --> 00:36:16,920
why some people choose other path.

481
00:36:21,200 --> 00:36:25,120
Anyway, thank you again
for helping my mother today.

482
00:36:27,040 --> 00:36:28,400
Go check on her.

483
00:36:32,920 --> 00:36:34,280
Go on.

484
00:36:46,280 --> 00:36:47,640
Feel better?

485
00:36:52,400 --> 00:36:54,160
You should wash your
face to feel refreshed.

486
00:37:14,200 --> 00:37:15,880
Why did you get so scared?

487
00:37:37,040 --> 00:37:39,080
While I was running in the forest,

488
00:37:43,040 --> 00:37:44,480
I heard the sound of a bomb.

489
00:37:46,986 --> 00:37:49,200
It brought back memories
of that day at the university.

490
00:37:51,960 --> 00:37:54,400
My friend was killed by a
bomb right in front of me.

491
00:38:05,400 --> 00:38:07,560
Haven't you forgotten what
happened at the university?

492
00:38:16,440 --> 00:38:18,600
I feel guilty that my friend was killed,

493
00:38:20,560 --> 00:38:22,600
and I still feel guilty for surviving.

494
00:38:40,920 --> 00:38:42,720
You know, it's not your fault.

495
00:38:51,480 --> 00:38:53,000
I get how you feel.

496
00:38:53,800 --> 00:38:55,480
No one can escape the guilt.

497
00:39:01,120 --> 00:39:02,600
Just keep holding on,

498
00:39:06,760 --> 00:39:08,240
and speak for your friend.

499
00:39:10,000 --> 00:39:11,360
Do it for him,

500
00:39:14,120 --> 00:39:15,960
the things he'll never
get a chance to do.

501
00:39:32,920 --> 00:39:34,760
Why do you smoke?

502
00:39:39,520 --> 00:39:41,160
Do you have anything on your mind?

503
00:39:46,560 --> 00:39:49,320
It's OK if you don't want
to share, I'm just asking.

504
00:39:56,680 --> 00:39:58,200
I saw the people I love,

505
00:39:59,880 --> 00:40:01,640
all of my comrades,

506
00:40:03,600 --> 00:40:05,000
die right in front of me.

507
00:40:10,080 --> 00:40:11,840
It happened everyday
until it became normal.

508
00:40:14,200 --> 00:40:15,279
I don't know yet,

509
00:40:15,280 --> 00:40:16,400
when it'll be my turn.

510
00:40:26,200 --> 00:40:27,279
This smoke...

511
00:40:27,280 --> 00:40:29,840
is like a reminder that I'm still alive.

512
00:40:42,400 --> 00:40:45,960
I guess... it's just an excuse
to make yourself look cool.

513
00:40:47,160 --> 00:40:48,560
Am I right?

514
00:40:59,800 --> 00:41:01,240
So, am I cool?

515
00:41:07,240 --> 00:41:08,240
Mm.

516
00:41:25,840 --> 00:41:28,279
They live hand-to-mouth here

517
00:41:28,280 --> 00:41:29,599
because they don't have money.

518
00:41:29,600 --> 00:41:31,920
Most of them forage for food
in the forests and mountains.

519
00:41:33,000 --> 00:41:34,840
How many families live here?

520
00:41:36,000 --> 00:41:39,680
I didn't count them,
but there were probably several dozen.

521
00:41:52,520 --> 00:41:54,000
Ask anything you want.

522
00:41:54,840 --> 00:41:57,000
Why did you bring us on a trip today?

523
00:42:00,680 --> 00:42:01,920
Who said we're on a trip?

524
00:42:02,680 --> 00:42:04,239
Comrade Ploeng trusts you

525
00:42:04,240 --> 00:42:06,880
to reach out to the
masses. We're here to work.

526
00:42:07,160 --> 00:42:09,000
I know. Just kidding.

527
00:42:09,440 --> 00:42:11,399
Our job is to invite as many
people as possible to join.

528
00:42:11,400 --> 00:42:14,040
The more people you win
over, the faster you'll win.

529
00:42:15,280 --> 00:42:17,360
To get someone to join us,

530
00:42:17,640 --> 00:42:19,160
you must learn to give first.

531
00:42:19,480 --> 00:42:22,280
Just wandering in, who's
going to join with you?

532
00:42:22,600 --> 00:42:23,920
Give?

533
00:42:23,960 --> 00:42:26,079
We don't even have
enough meat to eat ourselves,

534
00:42:26,080 --> 00:42:27,240
so how can we give to anyone?

535
00:42:30,640 --> 00:42:34,120
Give what you can. Eat just
enough, use just enough,

536
00:42:34,440 --> 00:42:35,719
The rest can be
shared with others.

537
00:42:35,720 --> 00:42:37,720
If you have nothing, go help them out.

538
00:42:38,200 --> 00:42:41,200
It's simple. Students like
you should understand.

539
00:42:43,640 --> 00:42:45,280
Hey! Help!

540
00:42:47,960 --> 00:42:49,760
Help! Help my child!

541
00:42:51,440 --> 00:42:53,040
Help my child!
